description: This file defines the interface for a SNMP plugin, including function prototypes for initialization, support checks, unloading, and memory management. It contains macro definitions, include guards, and C linkage specifications.

methods.name: COSA_Init
methods.description: Initializes the SNMP plugin with the maximum supported version and plugin info.

methods.name: COSA_Async_Init
methods.description: Asynchronously initializes the SNMP plugin with the maximum supported version and plugin info.

methods.name: COSA_IsObjectSupported
methods.description: Checks if a specified object name is supported by the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_Unload
methods.description: Unloads or cleans up resources for the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryCheck
methods.description: Performs a memory check related to the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryUsage
methods.description: Reports current memory usage related to the plugin.

methods.name: COSA_MemoryTable
methods.description: Displays or manages the plugin's memory table.
